      "content": "It might feel like endurance is the only option, but sometimes forcing yourself to keep going is exactly what allows small moments of healing or respite to emerge. It's not about waiting for cracks to appear, but about existing in a way that acknowledges the pain's existence, even if it's hard to feel anything but despair right now. Your existence doesn't have to justify or alleviate the pain, but it does have to keep being.",
